pageContext.claim: “Now we're up to almost 100 miles. And we're getting a lot of support not only from Honduras but from Guatemala, from El Salvador. We're getting tremendous support from Mexico. Mexico has got some difficult problems, as you know, but they are really helping us.”
pageContext.analysis: The administration replaced about 60 miles of barrier fencing, as of Aug. 2019. That’s not the same as a Trump’s promised wall or building a new wall.
